    ÛÛÛÛÛÛ Troubleshooting...   yah right ÛÛÛÛÛÛ
    ÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄÄ

    Well this section isn't very covering, but we try to explain
    those problems some users of VMP have encountered.

    We've had several complainings about running out of memory
    although having lots of memory attached on board. Well well
    well... let me put this straight... the thing is that VMP
    is based on using EMS memory. If you run your system
    without an Expanded Memory Manager like QEMM386, EMM386,
    386MAX etc. VMP finds only your base memory and if it runs
    out, like it usually does, you get the out of memory error.
        So what to do ? The answer is pretty obvious and simple.
    Use Expanded Memory Manager. Easiest way is to use DOS's
    Manager. Just add this line to your CONFIG.SYS:

    DEVICE=C:\DOS\EMM386.EXE RAM

    Remember that you must load HIMEM.SYS before loading
    EMM386.EXE.

    If you already had the EMM386.EXE loaded but with NOEMS
    parameter (this is commonly used to gain more upper memory)
    remove the NOEMS parameter.



